  "id": "019d286a-f2d8-78b2-92cd-46ac66aa3a56",
  "content": "## Post-Implementation Checklist\n\n## Notes for the Implementer\n\n1. **hnsw_rs API uncertainty**: The exact method signatures for `Hnsw::insert()`, `Hnsw::search()`, and `Neighbour` fields are based on docs research. If they don't match, consult [hnsw_rs docs](https://docs.rs/hnsw_rs/latest/hnsw_rs/) and adjust. The test-driven approach will catch mismatches immediately.\n\n2. **Redb version**: Using redb 2.x. The `TableDefinition` API and transaction patterns are stable. If `range()` on `&str` keys doesn't work exactly as shown, check [redb docs](https://docs.rs/redb/latest/redb/).\n\n3. **Ollama model name**: Ollama uses short model names (`nomic-embed-text`) not HuggingFace paths (`nomic-ai/nomic-embed-text-v1.5`). The config defaults reflect this difference.\n\n4. **HNSW stale vectors**: When `delete_scope` is called, vectors remain in the HNSW index but their Redb entries are deleted. The post-filter in `search()` naturally excludes them. `corvia rebuild` cleans up stale vectors by reconstructing the index from scratch.\n\n5. **SurrealDB compile time**: The `surrealdb` crate adds significant compile time. If working only on LiteStore code, use `cargo test -p corvia-kernel -- test_lite_store` to avoid recompiling the full workspace.",
  "source_version": "docs/rfcs/2026-03-01-m1.2-litestore.md",
